      <item>
        <title>PSI as expected</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[luisherranz]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>You don’t need to change anything. You should still use <code>@font-face</code> and add the smallest possible font to your project. I think going only with the <code>woff2</code> format is the best option because it’s supported in all browsers with the only exception of IE11: <a href="https://caniuse.com/#search=woff2">https://caniuse.com/#search=woff2</a>. It’s also the smallest format due to its compression. The only difference starting from the next version is that Frontity won’t embed the file in the HTML. But it will still serve it.</p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/psi-as-expected/1617/23">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
