        <title>PSI as expected</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[sir.louen]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p></p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/original/1X/3d746fb043cc97b28a1d3747ef2d1a720b839892.png" data-download-href="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/3d746fb043cc97b28a1d3747ef2d1a720b839892" title="image"><img src="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/1X/3d746fb043cc97b28a1d3747ef2d1a720b839892_2_674x500.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="8LEAxcRlQstNz8y9vS3EhcG1W9A" width="674" height="500" srcset="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/1X/3d746fb043cc97b28a1d3747ef2d1a720b839892_2_674x500.png, https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/original/1X/3d746fb043cc97b28a1d3747ef2d1a720b839892.png 1.5x, https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/original/1X/3d746fb043cc97b28a1d3747ef2d1a720b839892.png 2x" data-small-upload="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/1X/3d746fb043cc97b28a1d3747ef2d1a720b839892_2_10x10.png"></a></div><p></p>
<p>I’m still getting around 85-90 PSI both in Page Speed Insights and with Lighthouse report.</p>
<p>I saw in the twitter account a template made by a user based on frontity and it oscillates also between 85-91 PSI</p>
<p>From my experience with WPO I’ve seen that 90+ PSI standards are set extremely high. Obviously the experience with Frontity once loaded the page (even under 90+) is 10 times better than loading each static site separately but unfortunately this is not taken into account for this measurements that will be a thing in a couple of months.</p>
<p>With a plain WP site with Twenty Nineteen, 100 PSI is achievable.</p>
